<text top="288" left="676" width="1569" height="94" font="font2" id="p1_t4" reading_order_no="3" segment_no="0" tag_type="text">Aerial  Common  Sensor  aircraft  was  neither  the </text>
<text top="494" left="675" width="1566" height="100" font="font0" id="p1_t5" reading_order_no="4" segment_no="0" tag_type="text">to  the  U.S.  Army.  The  Army  desperately  needed </text>
<text top="598" left="206" width="2035" height="100" font="font0" id="p1_t6" reading_order_no="5" segment_no="0" tag_type="text">the  ACS  to  replace  its  Guardrails,  a  fleet  of  small,  piloted </text>
<text top="702" left="214" width="2037" height="100" font="font0" id="p1_t7" reading_order_no="6" segment_no="0" tag_type="text">reconnaissance  aircraft  that  first  began  flying in  the  mid-1970s. </text>
<text top="850" left="258" width="605" height="47" font="font3" id="p1_t8" reading_order_no="7" segment_no="7" tag_type="text">The  Army  was  so  keen  on  the  ACS, </text>
