<text top="1813" left="912" width="640" height="49" font="font5" id="p1_t62" reading_order_no="57" segment_no="2" tag_type="text">delays—it  was  actually  canceled.  Less </text>
<text top="1857" left="911" width="641" height="49" font="font5" id="p1_t63" reading_order_no="58" segment_no="2" tag_type="text">than  5  percent  of major  defense  programs </text>
<text top="1906" left="911" width="538" height="47" font="font3" id="p1_t64" reading_order_no="59" segment_no="2" tag_type="text">ever  suffer  that  fate,  the  GAO  says. </text>
<text top="1949" left="961" width="591" height="50" font="font4" id="p1_t65" reading_order_no="60" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">Problems  in  defense  acquisitions  have </text>
<text top="1995" left="912" width="649" height="50" font="font4" id="p1_t66" reading_order_no="61" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">existed  for  decades.  What’s  new  is  the  eco- </text>
<text top="2042" left="911" width="641" height="49" font="font5" id="p1_t67" reading_order_no="62" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">nomic  scale.  The  Pentagon  now  spends </text>
<text top="2087" left="913" width="640" height="50" font="font4" id="p1_t68" reading_order_no="63" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">about  $21  million  every hour to  develop  and </text>
<text top="2133" left="911" width="644" height="51" font="font12" id="p1_t69" reading_order_no="64" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">procure  new  defense  systems.  As  recently </text>
